 not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. As with any product, if irritation occurs, please discontinue use.</span></p>',359,'2012-05-21 16:56:23','2012-05-21 16:56:23'),(707,'Product Ingredients','<p><span>Supplement Facts</span><br /><span>Serving Size: 1 Caplique&trade; Capsule</span><br /><span>Servings per Container: 60</span><br /><br /><span>Amount per Serving</span><br /><span>Xanthigen&reg; proprietary blend 300 mg&nbsp;</span><br /><span>providing:</span><br /><span>brown seaweed (undaria pinnatifida, laminaria japonica) (providing 1,275 mcg fucoxanthin (min.)), pomegranate seed oil</span><br /><span>GreenSelect&reg; Phytosome 150 mg&nbsp;</span><br /><span>providing:</span><br /><span>green tea (camellia sinensis) extract (leaf) and soy lecithin phospholipids (standardized to contain 13% epigallocatechin gallate (EGCG))</span><br /><br /><span>Other Ingredients: medium chain triglycerides, vegetable capsule</span><br /><br /><span>Contains soy</span></p>\r\n<p><span><span>This encapsulated product contains no hidden coatings, excipients, binders, fillers, shellacs, artificial colors or fragrance. Contains no dairy, wheat, yeast, gluten, corn, sugar, starch, preservatives or hydrogenated oils.</span></span></p>',361,'2012-05-23 20:52:32','2012-05-23 20:52:32'),(708,'More Information','<p><span>Warning: Not recommended for pregnant or lactating women.</span></p>\r\n<p><span><span>Tamper Resistant: Use only if safety seal is intact.</span><br /><br /><span>STORE SEALED IN A COOL DRY AREA</span><br /><br /><span>Keep out of the reach of children.</span><br /><br /><span>*These statements have not been evaluated by the FDA. These products are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure or prevent any diseases.</span></span></p>',361,'2012-05-23 20:53:07','2012-05-23 20:53:07'),(709,'Product Ingredients','<p><span>Active Ingredients: Nicotine (21 mg) (per patch). Inactive Ingredients: Ethylene/Vinyl Acetate Copolymer, Polyisobutylene, High Density Polyethylene Between Clear Polyster Backings.</span></p>',362,'2012-05-24 14:33:19','2012-05-24 14:33:19'),(710,'More Information','<p>If you are under 18 years of age, ask a doctor before use.</p>\r\n<p>Before using this product, read the enclosed user\'s guide for complete directions and other information.</p>\r\n<p><strong>WARNINGS:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you are pregnant of breast-feeding, only use this medicine on the advice of your health care provider.</li>\r\n<li>Smoking can seriously harm your child.</li>\r\n<li>Try to stop smoking without using any nicotine replacement medicine.</li>\r\n<li>This medicine is believed to be safer than smoking. However, the risks to your child from this medicine are not fully known.</li>\r\n<li>Do not use if you continue to smoke, chew tobacco, use sniff, or use a nicotine gum or other nicotine containing products.</li>\r\n<li>Keep out of reach of children and pets.</li>\r\n<li>Used patches have enough nicotine to poison children and pets.</li>\r\n<li>If swallowed, get medical help or contact a Poison Control Center right away.</li>\r\n<li>Dispose of the used patches by folding sticky ends together and inserting in disposal tray in this box.</li>\r\n<li>Do not use if individual pouch is open or torn.</li>\r\n<li>Not for sale to those under 18 years of age.</li>\r\n<li>Proof of age required.</li>\r\n<li>Not for sale in vending machines or from any source where proof of age cannot be verified.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Ask a Doctor Before Use if:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You have heart disease, recent heart attack, or irregular heartbeat.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Nicotine can increase your heart rate;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>High blood pressure not controlled with medication.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Nicotine can increase your blood pressure;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>An allergy to adhesive tape or have skin problems because you are more likely to get rashes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Ask a Doctor or Pharmacist Before Use if:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You are using a non-nicotine stop smoking drug;</li>\r\n<li>Taking a prescription medicine for depression or asthma.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Your prescription dose may need to be adjusted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>When using this product do not smoke even when not wearing the patch. * The nicotine in your skin will still be entering your blood stream for several hours after you take off the patch;</li>\r\n<li>If you have vivid dreams or other sleep disturbances remove this patch at bedtime.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Stop use and ask a doctor if:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Skin redness caused by the patch does not go away after four days, or if your skin swells, or you get a rash</li>\r\n<li>Irregular heartbeat or palpitations occur</li>\r\n<li>You get symptoms of nicotine overdose such as nausea, vomiting, dizziness, weakness and rapid heartbeat</li>\r\n</ul>',362,'2012-05-24 14:34:46','2012-05-24 14:34:46'),(711,'Product Ingredients','<p><strong>Active Ingredients&nbsp;</strong><br /><span>Nicotine Polacrilex - 4 mgStop Smoking Aid</span><br /><br /><strong>Inactive Ingredients</strong><br /><span>Acesulfame Potassium , D&amp;C Yellow #10 Al. Lake , Gum Base , Magnesium Oxide , Menthol , Peppermint Oil , Sodium Carbonate , Xylitol</span></p>',363,'2012-05-24 14:58:02','2012-05-24 14:58:02'),(712,'More Information','<p><strong>If you are pregnant or breast-feeding, only use this medicine on the advice of your health care provider.</strong><span>Smoking can seriously harm your child. Try to stop smoking without using any nicotine replacement medicine. This medicine is believed to be safer than smoking. However, the risks to your child from this medicine are not fully known.&nbsp;</span><strong>Do not use</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you continue to smoke, chew tobacco, use snuff, or use a nicotine patch or other nicotine containing products</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Ask a doctor before use if you have</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A sodium-restricted diet</li>\r\n<li>Heart disease, recent heart attack, or irregular heartbeat. Nicotine can increase your heart rate.</li>\r\n<li>High blood pressure not controlled with medication. Nicotine can increase your blood pressure.</li>\r\n<li>Stomach ulcer or diabetes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Ask a doctor or pharmacist before use if you are</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Using a non-nicotine stop smoking drug</li>\r\n<li>Taking prescription medicine for depression or asthma. Your prescription dose may need to be adjusted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Stop use and ask a doctor if</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mouth, teeth or jaw&nbsp;problems occur</li>\r\n<li>Irregular heartbeat or palpitations occur</li>\r\n<li>You get symptoms of nicotine overdose such as nausea, vomiting, dizziness, diarrhea, weakness and rapid heartbeat</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Keep out of reach of children and pets.</strong><span>&nbsp;Nicotine lozenges may have enough nicotine to make children and pets sick. Wrap used pieces of gum in paper and throw away in the trash. In case of overdose, get medical help or contact a Poison Control Center right away.</span></p>',363,'2012-05-24 14:58:29','2012-05-24 14:58:29'),(719,'Product Ingredients','<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Supplement Facts</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Serving Size: 2 Gummies (6 g) Servings per bottle: 60</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Amount Per Serving % 2&ndash;4 yrs % 4+ yrs*</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Calories 20</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Calories from fat 0</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Total Fat 0 g &dagger; 0%</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Saturated Fat 0 g &dagger; 0%</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Trans Fat 0 g &dagger; &dagger;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Cholesterol 0 mg &dagger; 0%</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Sodium 10 mg &dagger; &lt;1%</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Total Carbohydrate 4.0 g &dagger; 1%</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Sugars 3.0 g &dagger; &dagger;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Total Omega-3s 82 mg &dagger; &dagger;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Total EPA and DHA 68 mg &dagger; &dagger;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">(Eicosapentaenoic Acid and Docosahexaenoic Acid)</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">* Percent Daily Values are based on a 2,000 calorie diet.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">&dagger; Daily Value not established.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Other Ingredients: organic tapioca syrup, organic evaporated cane juice, fish oil (from anchovies and sardines), porcine gelatin, pectin, citric acid, natural flavor, natural color (from annatto), sodium citrate.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Sour Coating: organic sucrose crystals, fumaric acid.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Manufactured in a facility certified to be free of allergens derived from milk, eggs, fish, shellfish, tree nuts, wheat, peanuts, and soy. No gluten or artificial colors or flavors.</span></span></p>',436,'2012-06-19 01:50:28','2012-06-19 01:50:28'),(720,'More Information','<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Label\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Store in a cool, dry place, away from sunlight. Do not take if tamper-evident seal is broken or missing. Keep out of the reach of children</span></span></p>',436,'2012-06-19 01:51:32','2012-06-19 01:51:32'),(721,'Product Ingredients','<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong><span>&nbsp;Lavandula Angustifolia (Lavender) Flower Water,&nbsp; Rosa Centifolia (Rose)&nbsp; Flower Water, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil (Argan Oil) , Adansonia Digitata Oil (Baobab Tree Oil),&nbsp; Punica Granatum Seed Oil (Pomegranate Seed Oil), Rosa Canina Fruit Oil (Rosehip Oil), Punica Granatum Sterols (Pomegranate Sterols), Hyaluronic Acid,&nbsp; Resveratrol, Ascorbic Acid,&nbsp;&nbsp; Xanthan Gum, Natapres (Glycerin, Leuconostoc/Radish Root Ferment Filtrate,&nbsp; Lonicera Japonica (Honeysuckle) Flower Extract, Lonicera Caprifolium (Honeysuckle) Extract,&nbsp; Populus Tremuloides Bark Extract, Gluconolactone.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>',437,'2012-06-25 22:27:13','2012-06-25 22:27:13'),(722,'About La Bedouine','<p>From a lavender field in France to a Berber village in Morocco</p>\r\n<p>La Bedouine is a story about love, magical elixirs, and the journey that is Life.</p>\r\n<p>A few years ago, I married a French man who I met in a medieval village in the south of France and at 50+&nbsp; began a new life in a foreign land.&nbsp; As a wedding gift a beautiful friend gave me a bottle of oil the color of the Provence sun.&nbsp; The oil was not from France, but from her native country, Morocco.&nbsp;&nbsp; It was, she said,&nbsp; L&rsquo;huile Argan.&nbsp; Argan Oil.&nbsp; Liquid Gold.</p>\r\n<p>I had never heard of Argan Oil or its reputation as a magic potion for the skin.&nbsp; At first I was reluctant, oil on my face? But it was surprisingly not greasy, and a few days later my skin, parched from the sirocco winds of Provence, was amazingly soft and supple.&nbsp; Not one dry patch!&nbsp; My friend surprised me again with another gift, a plastic bag filled with&nbsp;&nbsp; gold-colored gel.&nbsp; She told me to wash with these pulverized Argan nuts. This time I did not hesitate, and I was rewarded with skin so silken my camisole slipped off my shoulders.</p>\r\n<p>For over 25 years I&rsquo;d been an investigative journalist, an advocate for justice for animals and the under-served.&nbsp; I began a more personal quest: to find the source of these magical elixirs.</p>\r\n<p>Months later, I was driving along a winding coastal road toward an old port in southwest Morocco, the heart of Argan country. I saw white goats climbing Argan trees to eat the rare fruit and long limbed camels gazing seaward from pebbly shores.&nbsp; I&rsquo;d been told that Berber Women&rsquo;s Argan Oil Cooperatives were the source of Argan Oil, and I was on my way to buy from those equitable enterprises.</p>\r\n<p>What I discovered in the cinderblock buildings that housed the cooperatives I visited were sweat shop conditions . Women earned pennies and men took in the cash.&nbsp; Certainly there must be equitable cooperatives, I had seen photos of gaily garbed women cracking Argan nuts, but I could not find any along that road or in the many villages where I stopped.&nbsp;&nbsp; The investigative journalist in me began asking questions.&nbsp; I learned this:&nbsp; many cooperatives are simply photo opportunities for tourists. Most of the Argan Oil sold in the world market is produced in factories that dilute this oil with cheap blends. Even in the souks, I was warned, the Argan Oil is factory-made.</p>\r\n<p>My search for pure Argan Oil took me into the homes of Berber families who have been hand-milling this &ldquo;Liquid Gold&rdquo; for generations, if not centuries. They produce the oil in ancient stone querns, largely for their own families&nbsp; in small quantities.&nbsp; Photo stone quern These women also made the golden Argan gel that had silkened my skin.&nbsp; I packed kilos of gel and bottles of Argan Oil and back in Provence found local farms where the m&eacute;tier of growing Lavandin is part of the families&rsquo; age-old legacy.</p>\r\n<p>With respect for authenticity, tradition and the families who work on native soil &hellip;and with a new circle of women friends on three continents,&nbsp; La Bedouine was born.</p>',437,'2012-06-25 22:28:07','2012-06-25 22:28:07'),(723,'Testimonials','<p>Truthfully, as someone who often resents taking the time to wash my face at night when I would rather just go to bed, I actually take pleasure in bathing my face with La Bedouine cleanser. It has very smooth application and the fragrance brings an experience of timelessness. Yes, while cleaning the face! Afterwards my face feels fresh, clean but not scoured or dry, and the texture is silky smooth.</p>\r\n<p>-Virginia Guaraldo, New Hampshire</p>\r\n<p>I am not a products person but I am addicted to the cleanser and the masque!</p>\r\n<p>-Mike Nelson, North Carolina</p>\r\n<p>I love these products! Love the lavender smell in the cleanser!</p>\r\n<p>-Lee Stevens, Kansas</p>\r\n<p>I cannot live without the cleanser and masque. People are always commenting about how beautiful my skin is. It\'s never felt cleaner or smoother</p>\r\n<p>-Christina Christensen, Connecticut</p>\r\n<p>This is what I\'ve been looking for: an organic skin product that also benefits the indigenous women who make it by hand! Thank you La Bedouine.</p>\r\n<p>-Bonnie Cohen, North Carolina</p>\r\n<p>I love these products! I\'m over 70 and they honestly rejuvenate my skin so it feels baby soft!</p>\r\n<p>-Sandra Porst, California</p>',437,'2012-06-25 22:28:42','2012-06-25 22:28:42'),(724,'Product Ingredients','<p><strong>Ingredients:&nbsp;</strong><span>&nbsp;Sodium Arganate, Water, Lavandula Angustifolia (Lavender) Oil.</span></p>',439,'2012-06-25 22:38:40','2012-06-25 22:38:40'),(725,'About La Bedouine','<p>From a lavender field in France to a Berber village in Morocco</p>\r\n<p>La Bedouine is a story about love, magical elixirs, and the journey that is Life.</p>\r\n<p>A few years ago, I married a French man who I met in a medieval village in the south of France and at 50+&nbsp; began a new life in a foreign land.&nbsp; As a wedding gift a beautiful friend gave me a bottle of oil the color of the Provence sun.&nbsp; The oil was not from France, but from her native country, Morocco.&nbsp;&nbsp; It was, she said,&nbsp; L&rsquo;huile Argan.&nbsp; Argan Oil.&nbsp; Liquid Gold.</p>\r\n<p>I had never heard of Argan Oil or its reputation as a magic potion for the skin.&nbsp; At first I was reluctant, oil on my face? But it was surprisingly not greasy, and a few days later my skin, parched from the sirocco winds of Provence, was amazingly soft and supple.&nbsp; Not one dry patch!&nbsp; My friend surpris