ttles of Argan Oil and back in Provence found local farms where the m&eacute;tier of growing Lavandin is part of the families&rsquo; age-old legacy.</p>\r\n<p>With respect for authenticity, tradition and the families who work on native soil &hellip;and with a new circle of women friends on three continents,&nbsp; La Bedouine was born.</p>',439,'2012-06-25 22:39:09','2012-06-25 22:39:09'),(726,'Testimonials','<p>Truthfully, as someone who often resents taking the time to wash my face at night when I would rather just go to bed, I actually take pleasure in bathing my face with La Bedouine cleanser. It has very smooth application and the fragrance brings an experience of timelessness. Yes, while cleaning the face! Afterwards my face feels fresh, clean but not scoured or dry, and the texture is silky smooth.</p>\r\n<p>-Virginia Guaraldo, New Hampshire</p>\r\n<p>I am not a products person but I am addicted to the cleanser and the masque!</p>\r\n<p>-Mike Nelson, North Carolina</p>\r\n<p>I love these products! Love the lavender smell in the cleanser!</p>\r\n<p>-Lee Stevens, Kansas</p>\r\n<p>I cannot live without the cleanser and masque. People are always commenting about how beautiful my skin is. It\'s never felt cleaner or smoother</p>\r\n<p>-Christina Christensen, Connecticut</p>\r\n<p>This is what I\'ve been looking for: an organic skin product that also benefits the indigenous women who make it by hand! Thank you La Bedouine.</p>\r\n<p>-Bonnie Cohen, North Carolina</p>\r\n<p>I love these products! I\'m over 70 and they honestly rejuvenate my skin so it feels baby soft!</p>\r\n<p>-Sandra Porst, California</p>\r\n<p><span>I am totally pleased! I LOVE the way they smell and my skin feels so clean. I love the little jars. It\'s such a nice little ritual and I feel goddess-y! Thank you so much!&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>-Katie in Asheville, NC</span></p>\r\n<p>I think the cleanser is like liquid gold.</p>\r\n<p>-Stan in Chapel Hill, NC</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve seen significa