l (Baobab Tree Oil),&nbsp; Punica Granatum Seed Oil (Pomegranate Seed Oil), Rosa Canina Fruit Oil (Rosehip Oil), Punica Granatum Sterols (Pomegranate Sterols), Hyaluronic Acid,&nbsp; Resveratrol, Ascorbic Acid,&nbsp;&nbsp; Xanthan Gum, Natapres (Glycerin, Leuconostoc/Radish Root Ferment Filtrate,&nbsp; Lonicera Japonica (Honeysuckle) Flower Extract, Lonicera Caprifolium (Honeysuckle) Extract,&nbsp; Populus Tremuloides Bark Extract, Gluconolactone.</span></p>',477,'2012-07-19 00:53:14','2012-07-19 00:53:14'),(789,'Product Ingredients','<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong>&nbsp;Papaver rhoeas L (coquelicots), Punica Granatum (pomegranate). Purified Water.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pot:</strong>&nbsp;Sun-baked, Terracotta</p>\r\n<p><strong>100% botanical<br />No dyes<br />No chemicals</strong></p>',485,'2012-07-19 14:07:09','2012-07-19 14:07:09'),(790,'Product Ingredients','<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> Pure, 100%&nbsp; organic Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil.</p>',486,'2012-07-19 21:08:47','2012-07-19 21:08:47'),(791,'About La Bedouine','<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">From a lavender field in France to a Berber village in Morocco</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">La Bedouine is a story about love, magical elixirs, and the journey that is Life.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">A few years ago, I married a French man who I met in a medieval village in the south of France and at 50+&nbsp; began a new life in a foreign land.&nbsp; As a wedding gift a beautiful friend gave me a bottle of oil the color of the Provence sun.&nbsp; The oil was not from France, but from her native country, Morocco.&nbsp;&nbsp; It was, she said,&nbsp; L&rsquo;huile Argan.&nbsp; Argan Oil.&nbsp; Liquid Gold.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">I had never heard of Argan Oil or its reputation as a magic potion for the skin.&nbsp; At first I was reluctant, oil on my face? But it was surprisingly not greasy, and a few days later my skin, parched from the sirocco winds of Provence, was amazingly soft and supple.&nbsp; Not one dry patch!&nbsp; My friend surprised me again with another gift, a plastic bag filled with&nbsp;&nbsp; gold-colored gel.&nbsp; She told me to wash with these pulverized Argan nuts. This time I did not hesitate, and I was rewarded with skin so silken my camisole slipped off my shoulders.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">For over 25 years I&rsquo;d been an investigative journalist, an advocate for justice for animals and the under-served.&nbsp; I began a more personal quest: to find the source of these magical elixirs.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">Months later, I was driving along a winding coastal road toward an old port in southwest Morocco, the heart of Argan country. I saw white goats climbing Argan trees to eat the rare fruit and long limbed camels gazing seaward from pebbly shores.&nbsp; I&rsquo;d been told that Berber Women&rsquo;s Argan Oil Cooperatives were the source of Argan Oil, and I was on my way to buy from those equitable enterprises.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">What I discovered in the cinderblock buildings that housed the cooperatives I visited were sweat shop conditions . Women earned pennies and men took in the cash.&nbsp; Certainly there must be equitable cooperatives, I had seen photos of gaily garbed women cracking Argan nuts, but I could not find any along that road or in the many villages where I stopped.&nbsp;&nbsp; The investigative journalist in me began asking questions.&nbsp; I learned this:&nbsp; many cooperatives are simply photo opportunities for tourists. Most of the Argan Oil sold in the world market is produced in factories that dilute this oil with cheap blends. Even in the souks, I was warned, the Argan Oil is factory-made.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">My search for pure Argan Oil took me into the homes of Berber families who have been hand-milling this &ldquo;Liquid Gold&rdquo; for generations, if not centuries. They produce the oil in ancient stone querns, largely for their own families&nbsp; in small quantities.&nbsp; Photo stone quern These women also made the golden Argan gel that had silkened my skin.&nbsp; I packed kilos of gel and bottles of Argan Oil and back in Provence found local farms where the m&eacute;tier of growing Lavandin is part of the families&rsquo; age-old legacy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">With respect for authenticity, tradition and the families who work on native soil &hellip;and with a new circle of women friends on three continents,&nbsp; La Bedouine was born.</p>',486,'2012-07-19 21:11:08','2012-07-19 21:11:08'),(792,'Testimonials','<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">Truthfully, as someone who often resents taking the time to wash my face at night when I would rather just go to bed, I actually take pleasure in bathing my face with La Bedouine cleanser. It has very smooth application and the fragrance brings an experience of timelessness. Yes, while cleaning the face! Afterwards my face feels fresh, clean but not scoured or dry, and the texture is silky smooth.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">-Virginia Guaraldo, New Hampshire</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">I am not a products person but I am addicted to the cleanser and the masque!</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">-Mike Nelson, North Carolina</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">I love these products! Love the lavender smell in the cleanser!</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">-Lee Stevens, Kansas</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">I cannot live without the cleanser and masque. People are always commenting about how beautiful my skin is. It\'s never felt cleaner or smoother</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">-Christina Christensen, Connecticut</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">This is what I\'ve been looking for: an organic skin product that also benefits the indigenous women who make it by hand! Thank you La Bedouine.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">-Bonnie Cohen, North Carolina</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">I love these products! I\'m over 70 and they honestly rejuvenate my skin so it feels baby soft!</p>\r\n<p style=\"font: 12.72px/17.27px Ubuntu, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 0px; outline: 0px; border: 0px currentColor; color: #473e39; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: transparent; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">-Sandra Porst, California</p>',486,'2012-07-19 21:11:34','2012-07-19 21:11:34'),(793,'Product Ingredients','<p><strong>Mousse d\'Argan:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span>Sodium Arganate, Water, Lavandula Angustifolia (Lavender) Oil.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Creme d\'Argan:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span><span>Lavandula Angustifolia (Lavender) Flower Water,&nbsp; Rosa Centifolia (Rose)&nbsp; Flower Water, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil (Argan Oil) , Adansonia Digitata Oil (Baobab Tree Oil),&nbsp; Punica Granatum Seed Oil (Pomegranate Seed Oil), Rosa Canina Fruit Oil (Rosehip Oil), Punica Granatum Sterols (Pomegranate Sterols), Hyaluronic Acid,&nbsp; Resveratrol, Ascorbic Acid,&nbsp;&nbsp; Xanthan Gum, Natapres (Glycerin, Leuconostoc/Radish Root Ferment Filtrate,&nbsp; Lonicera Japonica (Honeysuckle) Flower Extract, Lonicera Caprifolium (Honeysuckle) Extract,&nbsp; Populus Tremuloides Bark Extract, Gluconolactone and Ubiquinone (CoEnzyme Q10).</span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>La Bedouine Argan Oil:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span><span><span>Pure, 100%&nbsp; organic Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil.</span></span></span></p>',488,'2012-08-20 05:04:15','2012-08-20 05:04:15'),(794,'Ingredients','<p><strong>Proprietary Blend: 350 mg&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong></strong><span>Carrot (root), calcium lactate, bovine liver, porcine stomach parenchyma, d