INSERT INTO `spree_posts` VALUES (5,'Water Works!','water-works',NULL,'2011-02-14 00:00:00','![](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/274/original/water.jpg \"\")\r\n\r\nI could easily start and end this post by simply saying, drink your water people! and that would be enough.  However, if I needed to do some convincing, this is what I would say:\r\n\r\nAbout 70% of our bodies are made up of water.\r\nAbout 3/4 of the population is chronically dehydrated.\r\nFor people with chronic joint and muscle pain, increased water can cause a drastic decrease in pain level.\r\nMost chronic migraine sufferers get better when their water increases.\r\nYou can decrease your risk of breast, colon and bladder cancer by drinking 8 glasses of water per day.\r\nChronic constipation is usually significantly helped by increasing water.\r\nPeople on a weight loss program will see a reduction in cravings, hunger and desire for sweet and salty foods if they drink more water!  Dehydration will also decrease metabolism and make weight loss difficult.\r\nOverall energy increases when you drink more water, so people with fatigue issues generally feel better with more water.\r\nChildren are often at a higher risk for dehydration because most of their dietary fluids tend to be drinks and juices instead of water.\r\nYour body tends to hold on to water, causing more boating when you are dehydrated.\r\nYou can go without food for weeks and stay alive, but you can only make it a few days without water.\r\nMost of the biochemical reactions essential to life, involve water.\r\n\r\nNow, if those are not enough reasons for you to start drinking more water, then you may have to give my office a call so we can have a chat!\r\n\r\nOnce you decide to increase your water, there are generally a long list of questions that will most likely sound like this:\r\n\r\nI dont have enough time at work to keep running to the bathroom.  Every time  I start drinking more water, my bathroom trips get more frequent To answer that, I say.thats how your body works.  If it isnt used to getting that amount of water, the first response is to get rid of it.  Unfortunately, you cant change that.  Try to drink more at times where it is convenient for you to use the bathroom.  After a few weeks of your new water regime, your body quickly adjusts and your bathroom visits will decrease!\r\n\r\nWell, what kind of water should I drink?  There are so many choices out there, bottled, distilled, alkaline pH, well water, tap, filtered, sports water, flavored water I agree, the choices for the type of water to drink are overwhelming. I drink a mixture of filtered water directly from the tap and bottled water when I am not at home.  Water that has color and flavor is a mixed drink!  Its not water.  There are many commercial products that add all sorts of chemicals to water in order to make it more appealing.  I am not sure what the resulting beverage is, but I assure you, it is no longer water.  Sports drinks do not replace water.  Try to drink as much regular water as possible.  Tap water, and maybe even most bottled water, is polluted and contaminated with all sorts of nasty things that I wont go into right now.  However, if you are healthy, and your body is working the way it should, your natural detoxification mechanisms can usually handle it.  Try not to reuse disposable plastic water bottles for drinking water.  You can reuse them in other ways or recycle them.  Water is just about neutral pH.  Drink regular water, it should not be modified in any way, alkaline or acidic water may have been reported to have magical effects but nothing beats the real thing.\r\n \r\nWell how much do I really need?  There is water in food, and drinks.  Can that count towards my daily intake? Water in the foods you eat will obviously affect your body and improve your hydration level.  However, that recommended half your body weight in ounces, should be pretty much plain old regular water.  Tea doesnt count, neither does coffee or fruits or any of the brightly colored flavored beverages you see in the grocery store.  For instance, bread contains water,  but it would be silly to go out and eat a bunch of bread and say, I had my share of water today!.  If the weather is warm, or if you workout a lot you, will need to drink a little more than half your body weight in ounces.\r\n\r\nWater is mystical, pure, delicious and an essential component of good nutrition.  In the holistic view of life, water connects everything on earth.  The earth itself is mostly covered by water and magnificent rivers and streams flow into great oceans.  Water cycles from liquid, to vapor to ice and each state plays a specific role in the balance of the earth.  There are animals and plants that live entirely submerged in water and they would die if we took them out of that environment.  As humans, our entire fetal development is done in water-like fluid.  The health benefits of water are so many, all our research and technologies have barely touched the surface of this magnificent, life giving substance.  Drink plenty of pure, un-fooled around with water everyday.  As I said before, drink your water people and feed your children water!\r\n\r\n-Dr.Parkes',NULL,1,'2012-05-08 18:37:33','2012-05-17 15:55:38',1),(6,'Most Toxic Fruits and Vegetables','most-toxic-fruits-and-vegetables',NULL,'2011-09-16 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/275/medium/apple.jpg?1337268045 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nToday, most fruits and vegetables on the market are commercially grown and mass-produced in order to meet the demands of a growing population. Unfortunately, in the effort to produce crops faster, avoiding pests and disease, many different pesticides are used. These pesticides can have a wide variety of ill effects on the human body once they start to accumulate. Some health problems clearly linked to pesticide exposure include; cancer, Parkinsons disease, fertility problems, birth defects, childhood cancers, hormonal problems. According to the Environmental working group (EWG), the average person ingests about 15 different pesticides per day.\r\n\r\nThe 20 most toxic items:\r\n\r\n  - Peaches\r\n  - Apples\r\n  - Sweet Bell Peppers\r\n  - Celery\r\n  - Nectarines\r\n  - Strawberries\r\n  - Cherries\r\n  - Pears\r\n  - Grapes (Imported)\r\n  - Spinach\r\n  - Lettuce\r\n  - Potatoes\r\n  - Carrots\r\n  - Green Beans\r\n  - Hot Peppers\r\n  - Cucumbers\r\n  - Raspberries\r\n  - Plums\r\n  - Grapes (Domestic)\r\n  - Oranges\r\n\r\nSo, now what?\r\n\r\nSince you must eat fruits and vegetables, there are a few choices.\r\na) Buy organic produce. Organic produce is much less contaminated and they honestly taste better.\r\nb) Buy locally grown produce. If you live in a place where the weather permits local farming and farmers markets, thats a great way to get good food and avoid toxins.\r\nc) Wash everything. Meticulous washing can help remove a large number of contaminants.\r\nd) Peel/ remove the skin. This is not a great option, since many nutrients are found in the outer layers of fruits and vegetables. However, removing this layer can significantly decrease your toxic burden.',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 15:20:21','2012-05-17 15:55:58',1),(7,'Dont Sweat the Scale!','don-t-sweat-the-scale',NULL,'2011-10-06 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/276/medium/scale.jpg?1337268393 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nThis week, I have had some concerns from people who have been doing everything right in order to lose weight. They are working out, eating well, getting adequate sleep and keeping their stress levels low. They hop on my scale and say Doc, I dont understand, I have been good all week and I havent lost much weight!.\r\n\r\nI wish I knew why some people could just skip a meal and walk around the block and end up losing 10 lbs while others do everything right and only see tiny changes if any, on the scale. I got frustrated years ago with asking why, so I stopped. It really doesnt matter. Thats just how it is. What you can do with that information, if you are one of those people who needs to go the extra mile, is, get up and do it. Do the extra workout, be very careful with your food and just accept that as a part of the wonderful uniqueness that is you.\r\n\r\nNow having said that, here are a few things that I have noticed that may help explain the numbers on the scale:\r\n\r\n- Whenever you lose inches, especially on your waist and hips, your weight loss on the scale slows down. Vice versa is also true.\r\n- Body composition is much more important than weight, so sometimes you lose fat and gain muscle which improves your body composition but doesnt show up on the scale. You end up being smaller but not weighing much less!\r\n- Slow and steady wins the race. I would love to see everyone have huge, dramatic weight loss results week after week however, healthy, sustainable wight loss is a process and in order to keep it off for life, it should come off in a steady, consistent fashion. In fact, losing more than a few pounds per week, (unless you have more than 100 lbs to lose) can be quite dangerous.\r\n- Whenever there is an increase in exercise, the change on the scale tends to show up about two weeks later (so much for instant gratification!).\r\n- Not seeing changes on the scale can be a big de-motivator. So, dont get on the scale everyday! Your weight can fluctuate several pounds in the same day!\r\n- As long diet and exercise are consistent, the weight soon has no choice but to submit and fall off. The people who stick to the plan despite the temperament of the scale, usually end up meeting their weight loss goals.\r\n\r\n-Dr. Parkes',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 15:27:56','2012-05-17 15:56:14',1),(8,'Yoga for Anxiety and Depression','yoga-for-anxiety-and-depression',NULL,'2011-10-10 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/277/medium/yoga.jpg?1337268655 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nSince the 1970s, meditation and other stress-reduction techniques have been studied as possible treatments for depression and anxiety. One very ancient practice, yoga, has become increasingly popular in recent decades. The origin of yoga predates written history and it appears to work very well when done regularly.\r\n\r\nWhat is Yoga?\r\nThe word Yoga comes from the Sanskrit word Yuj meaning to yoke, join or unite. This implies joining or integrating all aspects of the individual  body with mind and mind with soul  to achieve a happy, balanced and useful life. Alternately, yoga can be thought of as a form of exercise that can increase mental clarity and put you in touch with your body by intentionally increasing awareness and mindfulness.\r\n\r\nYoga classes can vary from gentle and accommodating to strenuous and challenging. The choice of style tends to be based on physical ability and personal preference. Hatha yoga, the most common type of yoga practiced in the United States, combines three elements: physical poses, called asanas; controlled breathing practiced in conjunction with asanas; and a short period of deep relaxation or meditation.\r\n\r\nHow it works\r\nBy reducing perceived stress and anxiety, yoga appears to modulate stress response systems. This, in turn, decreases physiological arousal  for example, reducing the heart rate, lowering blood pressure, and easing respiration. In a German study published in 2005, 24 women who described themselves as emotionally distressed took two 90-minute yogaclasses a week for three months. At the end of three months, the women reported improvements in perceived stress, depression, anxiety, energy, fatigue, and well-being. Depression scores improved by 50%, anxiety scores by 30%, and overall well-being scores by 65%. Many Initial complaints of headaches, back pain, and poor sleep quality also resolved.\r\n\r\nIn cultures where yoga is practiced regularly by a large percentage of the population, the incidence of anxiety and depression is significantly less than in the United States.\r\n\r\nGetting Started\r\nStart slowly. If you have physical limitations, be sure to avoid poses that cause pain. You can choose to do yoga at home using a DVD or by attending a class at your local gym or yoga studio. Make sure you get a non-slip yoga mat and wear comfortable clothes.',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 15:32:34','2012-05-17 15:56:31',1),(9,'Ask Dr. Parkes','ask-dr-parkes',NULL,'2011-10-11 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/278/large/kparkes.jpg?1337268954 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nDear Dr. Parkes,\r\nWhat is the best way to reduce stress?\r\n P.M\r\n\r\nDear P.M,\r\nOne proven way to help the way your body handles stress is movement. A combination of vigorous and calming activity can help improve your energy, elevate your mood and help you better handle stress.\r\nPractices like yoga or tai chi help you clear your mind and focus in the moment. This inner calm helps you to relax.\r\nCardiovascular exercises like walking, jogging or biking will cause increased amounts of the hormones that help you feel good overall.\r\nFor best results, alternate the days you do calming exercises with the days you perform more vigorous exercises. Start with 15  20 minutes per day and work your way up to 45 minutes or an hour. Ideally you should aim to exercise 4  6 days per week.\r\n\r\nDear Dr. Parkes,\r\nI have tried to eat healthy and exercise but I never get anywhere because I am addicted to sugar. Help!\r\nK.H\r\n\r\nDear K.H,\r\nSugar and salt cravings are usually symptoms of an imbalance in the body. The most common reasons are poor functioning adrenal glands, vitamin/mineral deficiency (especially magnesium and chromium), blood sugar irregularities such as diabetes or hypoglycemia and poor eating habits. Too much sugar in the diet causes fatigue, sleep problems, constipation, weight gain, high cholesterol and a host of other problems. Sugar addiction is very real and the best way to fix it is to find out the root cause. Then, slowly start replacing refined sugar, deserts and candy with natural sugar found abundantly in fresh fruit. Eat small meals throughout the day comprised of vegetables and protein to help keep blood sugar balanced. Make sure that you take steps to reduce stress and incorporate a daily whole food multivitamin such as Catalyn that can be purchase at the Wellness Center.\r\n\r\nDear Dr. Parkes,\r\nMy mother is a chronic joint and muscle pain sufferer. She takes medicine but still complains. Is there anything she can do in her everyday life to help?\r\n J.O\r\n\r\nDear J.O,\r\nHere are some of my top choices for relieving chronic pain. Depending on your mothers particular situation, she can try one or all of them.\r\n*Gentle moderate exercise  This can improve circulation and oxygenate joints and muscles to relieve pain. Try, yoga or Tai Chi.\r\n*Warm Epsom salt baths  This relaxing treat helps soothe aching muscles and relieve tension. It can also drastically improve sleep when done in the evening or at night.\r\n*Adding spices like garlic and ginger to the diet with an intake of high quality fish oils can significantly reduce inflammation in the body which may lead to a reduction in pain.\r\n \r\n\r\nSubmit your wellness questions to Dr. Parkes by sending an email to cpmhwellness@gmail.com',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 15:38:44','2012-05-17 15:56:46',1),(10,'ADHD & Food Sensitivities','adhd-food-sensitivities',NULL,'2011-10-19 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/279/medium/foodallergy.jpg?1337269249 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nMany parents will quickly acknowledge that too much soda and candy makes their kids bounce off the walls on a sugar high, but what if a childs persistent hyperactivity was caused by milk, tomatoes, eggs, gluten or some other seemingly innocuous food? That is what a Dutch study published in January 2011 found: In kids with ADHD, researchers found that putting them on a restrictive diet to eliminate possible, previously unknown food sensitivities decreased hyperactivity for 64 percent of kids. In the study, of the 41 kids who completed the elimination diet, 32 saw decreased symptoms. When certain foods thought to be triggers for each child were reintroduced, most of the children relapsed. The eliminated diets, which lasted five weeks, consisted predominantly of rice, white meat and vegetables. Among 50 kids given a control diet that was just a standard, healthy diet for children, significant changes were not noted.  Given these findings; Jan Buitelaar, the lead author of the Dutch study and a psychiatrist at the Center, recommended that the elimination diet become part of standard of care for children with ADHD.\r\n\r\nWhat are food sensitivities?\r\n\r\nFood sensitivities are not the same as food allergies.  Some food allergies have an immediate outward reaction such as itching, swelling or hives.  However, food sensitivities are silent reactions to food that can sometimes cause unusual symptoms.  Some of these symptoms are headache, nausea, pain, sleepiness abnormal behavior and cognitive impairment.  These symptoms can easily be confused with other diseases.  Since there are no accurate laboratory tests that can consistently identify food sensitivities, without elimination and later reintroduction of foods, it is very difficult to figure out what foods are the triggers.\r\n\r\nWhat can you do?\r\n\r\nThe challenge with the elimination diet is that parents usually find it difficult to follow especially when the affected child is in a larger family.  However, simple steps can be taken with the guidance of a qualified health care provider that will make the transition easier for the entire family. Avoiding food sensitivities can significantly improve the symptoms of ADHD and it works well with any other therapy or treatment. \r\n\r\nFor more information please call the Carolina Partners Wellness Center at 919-792-3940.',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 15:42:26','2012-05-17 15:57:01',1),(11,'10 Ways to Reduce Breast Cancer Risk','10-ways-to-reduce-breast-cancer-risk',NULL,'2011-10-20 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/280/large/BC.png?1337269460 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\n- Diet  Eating whole, locally grown foods and avoiding packaged, processed, food will decrease exposure to chemicals such as food additives and pesticides. Eating a diet rich in greens such as kale, spinach, brussel sprouts and broccoli will help your body recycle and detoxify hormones that can lead to breast cancer.\r\n\r\n- Limit Microwave Use  Microwaves work by sending powerful radiation through food in order to quickly heat them up.  When food is microwaved (especially in in plastics), they become more toxic. On the occasion where a microwave is necessary, heat food in a ceramic container instead of plastic.\r\n\r\n- Quit Smoking  Women who smoke increse their risk of breast cancer.\r\n\r\n- [Get Vitamin D](http://66.228.62.131/t/categories/vitamins-and-minerals/vitamin-d \"\")  Vitamin D reduces the risk of breast cancer. Vitamin D is made in the skin when it is exposed to the sun. Women who limit exposure to the sun by wearing sunscreens are often low in vitamin D.\r\n\r\n- Use more  natural cosmetics  Chemicals such as Parabens and Phthalates are widely used in makeup, nail polish and skincare products.  These chemicals act as hormone disruptors and can increase risk in women with underlying hormone imbalances.\r\n\r\n- Avoid Taking Hormones  Most breast cancers are hormone sensitive.  Taking extra  hormones in the form of birth control or as hormone replacement therapy can disrupt the bodys natural hormonal balance.  It has been shown that some forms of hormone replacement therapy can increase breast canceer risk by as much as 75%.\r\n\r\n- Exercise  Research shows exercising regularly at a moderate or intense level for 4 to 7 hours per week lowers the risk of breast cancer. Exercise consumes and controls blood sugar and limits blood levels of insulin-like growth factor, a hormone that can affect how breast cells grow and behave.\r\n\r\n- Avoid radiation  Exopsure to radiation such as x-rays, to the face, neck and chest have been shown to increase risk.\r\n\r\n- Maintain a healthy weight  Women with a BMI greater than  27 have an increased risk.  Having a diet low in sugar and processed foods will help reduce excess body fat.\r\n\r\n- Avoid artificial sweeteners  Artificial sweetners such as Splenda and Sweet NLow are found in diet drinks and many zero calorie beverages.  These chemicals have a toxic effect in the liver and can increase risk.',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 15:48:05','2012-05-21 18:47:52',1),(12,'The Price of Convenience','the-price-of-convenience',NULL,'2011-10-25 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/281/medium/hospital.jpg?1337269798 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nEverybody is on the go. Events are scheduled. Kids have play dates, sports practice, field trips, musical performances, dance classes and a host of other events. Adults have airplanes to catch, emails to send, conference calls, meetings, presentations, gym, kids to pick up and schedules to coordinate. Each activity has to start and end on time in order to preserve the delicate sequence of order that is calendared into each day. In order for this fast paced activity-packed existence to work, there is one thing that has to exist, convenience. Everything must be convenient. Things have to be quick, efficient and easy. Herein lies the problem. Convenience is very expensive. I wasnt going to write this article because its too long, and I didnt think it would be convenient for people to read it. In the end, the ultimate price is our time, years deducted from lives. The very time people spend their lives trying to save is generally cut short as payment for convenience.\r\n\r\nConvenience\r\n\r\nDrive thru restaurants, prepackaged meals, precut fruits and vegetables, frozen food, fast food, 10 minute work outs, ATMs, gym equipment, remote controls, email, microwaves, text messages, prescription drugs, dry cleaning, washers and dryers, cars, plastic water bottles, immunizations, pesticides, genetically modified food, high fructose corn syrup, preservatives, trans fats, baby food, c-sections, vitaminsand this list could continue for days.\r\n\r\nWhats the big deal anyway?\r\n\r\nTechnology is great. Without computers, I dont know if I could function. I most certainly wouldnt be able to figure out how to get thousands of people to access the information I am providing here. Over the years, great inventions such as cars, washers and dryers and ATMs have certainly revolutionized society and we gladly pay for these conveniences. While many conveniences are an integral part of living in todays world, we must stop and think objectively about them. Take a car for example. People pay thousands of dollars plus, maintenance fees, taxes, auto insurance and fuel charges just to own a car. Cars help with efficient travel and makes commuting possible for many. Beyond the obvious costs associated with owning a car however, we often forget the effect of the emissions on the air and the wars currently being fought over oil. Closer to home though, we neglect to realize that walking or biking down to the pharmacy or store sometimes, instead of driving, could reduce the ill effects on the environment and provide us with much needed exercise. This could significantly impact the incidence of obesity, diabetes, heart disease and cancer. Hanging up clothes to dry when possible, could significantly cut fuel costs and again, decrease the demands on the environment. 10 minute workouts? Seriously? No, seriously? Emails and text messages have decreased inter-human interaction significantly. While it may be a good way for doing business, and it continues to weaken relationships between friends and families. Face time is an integral part of developing familial bonds. Conversations take on a whole new meaning when they take place in person. Family values, traditional recipes, love and affection dont translate well via text message or email. A smiley face doesnt quite do it. This is quite a hefty price to pay. Of course, one of the most inconvenient things is to be sick, so doctors prescribe billions of dollars worth of toxic drugs that are aimed at hiding the symptoms of disease each year. The practice of medicine has become so convenient that doctors can spend a few minutes with a patient they never met, and prescribe a drug with well-known toxic effects aka side effects and everyone accepts this as normal. Babies are given massive doses of antibiotics, steroids, immunizations and synthetic formula soon after birth in the name of convenience. Breast-feeding is quite inconvenient. Who has time for that? How are women supposed to work, pick up the older kids and keep everything on schedule if they have to feed a baby every 2  3 hours? Pediatricians advise mothers to feed their children synthetic formulas made from cows milk. This continues to be one of the most devastating things for young digestive systems. There is no substitute for breast milk.\r\n\r\nLets get REAL\r\n\r\nNow lets talk about the real assault on the lives of children and adults. It is convenient food. Most people dont cook regularly. When they do cook, it often involves, canned or frozen food and a microwave. I could spend pages talking about the sugar, fat and genetic modifications in convenience foods, but most people are already aware that these foods are not good. In fact, they are terrible and decrease life expectancy with every bite. I recently saw apples sliced and packaged conveniently. I was given a packet, and since I am not accustomed to eating that sort of thing, I could literally taste a bitterness on the skin. Still not sure how many chemicals I ate with my apple that day. Is it so inconvenient to wash and cut up an apple? A friend of mine left a turkey sandwich out accidentally. As an experiment, she decided to leave it alone to see what would happen. It was in a plastic sandwich bag and, 3 months later, it still looked good. That begs the question, what are we eating? The answer is, nobody knows. Real food should go bad after some time. When I buy organic apples, and leave them in my fruit bowl in the kitchen, they start to go bad after 4 or 5 days. The times when I purchase regular apples, they can last for weeks under the same conditions. You might say, this isnt so bad, we cant go around wasting food, it good that things last longer. To that, I say, what are we are we eating? Many foods are now genetically modified to resist disease, slow down aging, improve color and last longer. Strawberries, for example have DNA from fish put into them through biochemical engineering so they can last through the cold winter months. There is something inherently unsettling about that. What are we eating? It looks like a strawberry sitting on top of your cheesecake, but is it?\r\n\r\nSince we are talking about genes and genetic changes, I would be remise if I didnt talk about the number one, most convenient thing of all time, the microwave. It can be found in almost every home, restaurant, hotel and school. This little machine uses electricity and radiation to heat up the ice-cold food in seconds! Its magic, or the closest thing we have to magic. Personally, the idea, that you can put something ice cold in a machine that is not hot and 60 seconds later this item can be hot enough to severely burn you without the machine itself getting hot, is a little scary. How does it work? The radiation vibrates water molecules at super high speeds creating heat, which increase the temperature of the foods being zapped. Whats wrong with that? Lets see, microwaves are still banned form home use in some countries today because of the dangerous effects. The vibration of the molecules can cause bonds in the chemical structure of the food to break and sometimes recombine in different ways. So you put chicken in the microwave and you have no idea what comes out. It looks like chicken, but is it? What did you just create? What are you feeding your children? Nobody knows. Actually, studies have shown that d-Nitrosodiethanolamine (a well-known cancer-causing agent) is formed when you heat up meat in a microwave. Thats just one thing on a very long list. Added to the fact that most foods have already been genetically altered, this microwave phenomenon could feasibly make a bad situation much worse, and it does. Mothers will heat up an infants synthetic, genetically modified, chemical formula in a microwave. Yikes! Wait, radiation? Isnt radiation what they use to kill cancer? Doesnt radiation make you sick? Well according to the makers of microwaves, this is good radiation. It wont harm you at all. Bottom line. Stop it. Cook food, on a stove top, a convection oven or toaster oven. The few minutes you save isnt worth trading for the years you will probably spend being sick or the time you might lose if you die early. The cost is too high. Of all the avoidable conveniences, the microwave is the most dangerous but it is the easiest to avoid.\r\n\r\nOkay, so what do we do?\r\n\r\nWe cant possibly live in this society and not use the conveniences available, can we? Actually, there are a few closed societies that do just that. The Amish and Native Americans have managed to do it very successfully. While there arent very accurate data due to their privacy standards, I am willing to bet that 70% of the people living in these societies arent dying of heart disease, cancer, prescription drugs, diabetes or obesity. Fact: 70% of all people in our convenient society die from complications with the above problems. I am also willing to guess that Native American and Amish children arent obese or suffering from cancer, depression, ADD, ADHD or autism at the same alarming rate that kids outside of those societies are. It may be a wild theory, but could it be that all the things that we do for convenience could be causing the decline in health that we see today?\r\n\r\nIts not working and its not worth it.\r\n\r\nLets face it. Billions of dollars in technology and years of research and development has led us to where we are today. Fatter, sicker, more drugged up, tired, addicted to caffeine/nicotine, sad and even more depressed with no time to even think about reality. Ironically, convenience has made us busier than ever. While we cant avoid all conveniences, we must stop to evaluate which ones are necessary and which ones we can sometimes do without. Using a microwave occasionally, is certainly better than using it everyday. Walking, biking or using public transportation is better that driving everywhere. Buying and preparing wholesome organic or locally grown foods is better that eating from a drive thru, or buying pre-packaged, frozen meals. Pouring yourself a glass of water is better than dumping thousands of plastic bottles that release chemicals into the environment. Small changes can truly make a big difference. Start by picking one thing and working on that. Technology and convenience is a part of our lives. There are certainly many cases where it is a good thing. However, moderation is always key. Not everything should be convenient. We have to live with the costs to our health, environment and relationships. Our children and grand children will have to deal with the real consequences later. Its definitely not worth it.',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 15:52:05','2012-05-17 15:57:43',1),(13,'Boost Your Weight Loss with Intervals','boost-your-weight-loss-with-intervals',NULL,'2011-10-25 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/282/medium/workout.jpg?1337270349 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nInterval training is a good way to burn a lot of calories in a short amount of time.  This type of cardiovascular exercise focuses on alternating periods of very high intensity with periods of lower intensity.  The result is an increased calorie burn that continues even after the workout is complete.  Most cardiovascular exercises can be done as intervals.  A few of my favorites are walk/run, biking, eliptical, jump rope, stepper and rowing machine.\r\n\r\nHere are a few guidelines for doing intervals:\r\n\r\nAlways warm up and stretch for a few minutes before you begin.\r\n\r\nBeginner:  Low intensity  2 mins.   High intensity  1 min.  You should do a total of  5-7 rounds then cool down.\r\n\r\nIntermediate: Low intensity 1 min.   High Intensity  1 min.  You should do a total of  10 -12 rounds then cool down.\r\n\r\nAdvanced:  Low intensity 30 secs.   High Intensity  90 secs.  You should do a total of  12-15 rounds then cool down.\r\n\r\nIf you are not exhausted at the end of your rounds, it means your intensity level isnt high enough.  You should either increase your intensity or move to a more advanced level.',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 16:08:31','2012-05-21 18:46:16',1),(14,'What to do for the flu?','what-to-do-for-the-flu',NULL,'2011-10-26 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/283/medium/flu.jpg?1337270940 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nPrevention is the BEST medicine!  They key is to be and stay healthy!  Here are some helpful tips:\r\n\r\n- Get plenty of sleep\r\n\r\n- Drink plenty of water\r\n\r\n- Limit sweets\r\n\r\n- Eat good fats\r\n\r\n- Have homemade chicken stock (using apple cider vinegar)\r\n\r\n- Take a good multivitamin such as [Standard Processs Catalyn](http://66.228.62.131/products/catalyn \"\")\r\n\r\nEven in the best circumstances, you may still come down with a cold or flu.  There are two things I would have in my medicine chest for just such an occasion.  All supplements mentioned are available at our Wellness Center at 1011 Dresser Court:\r\n\r\nCongaplex: Congaplex is a supplement that supports the Thymus, which is the critical gland in antibody production and transforming white cells into infection-fighting killer cells.   Congaplex also provides real vitamins A, C, J, K, bioflavonoids, fish oil (a good fat!), Calcium Lactate (the easiest calcium for your body to utilize), magnesium and more.  It is derived from organically grown plants and processed in a way that keeps all of the vital forces intact.   Congaplex should be considered an essential part of your healthcare regime during flu season, particularly if you are prone to fevers and infections.\r\n\r\nAt the first sign of flu or cold symptoms take 2 Congaplex per waking hour for 48 hours.  This will almost always stop the problem.  Congaplex is even safe for infants and children; every 2 hours will almost always bring a fever back to normal within 8-12 hours and ends most colds and flu in 1-2 days.  It can also be used at the first sign of an ear infection.\r\n\r\nThe second product I recommend is a homeopathic product called [Oscillococcinum](http://66.228.62.131/products/oscillococcinum-6-doses \"\").  At the first sign of flu, open a small bottle and drop a few pellets into the mouth.   The directions suggest a whole bottle each time, but that is more than is necessary.  Follow the directions for how often.  Oscillococcinum is safe for all ages.\r\n\r\nFOR MORE INFORMATION, CALL CAROLINA PARTNERS WELLNESS CENTER OR ASK THE FRONT DESK STAFF TO SET UP A CONSULTATION WITH DR. PARKES!\r\n\r\n919-792-3940',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 16:12:02','2012-05-17 16:12:02',1),(15,'Beat the Sugar Blues','beat-the-sugar-blues',NULL,'2011-11-28 00:00:00','![REPLACE-WITH-ALT](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/284/medium/dessert.jpg?1337271360 \"REPLACE-WITH-TITLE\")\r\n\r\nCookies, cakes, brownies, ice cream, candy, soda, pies, and hot chocolate: it never ends. At this time of year, we are bombarded with high sugar treats, from Halloween through the Holidays.  Sugar is even hidden in foods we normally wouldnt even consider, like sauces, sandwiches and soups.\r\n\r\nHigh blood sugar levels have a direct impact on our overall health.  It can cause numerous health issues such as diabetes, high cholesterol, migraines, cancer, constipation and weight gain.  Less noticeably, high blood sugar can cause depression or worsen mood disorders.  The infamous sugar high is usually followed by a low or crash that cause feelings of sadness, fatigue and hopelessness. It is also shown that sugar contributes to hyperactivity and attention problems in young children and teens. In a study conducted in Great Britain, 80% of people with mood disorders noticed that food choices affected how they felt. They named sugar as a food stressor, and supportive foods were water, vegetables, fruits, and oil-rich fish.\r\n\r\nIn his book. The Brain Chemistry Diet, Dr. Michael Lesser says that reducing refined carbohydrates such as white sugar and corn syrup, will keep the blood sugar and accompanying mood swings under control. \r\n\r\nA diet that has an overabundance of refined sugar is usually deficient in essential nutrients like; B vitamins, vitamin C, zinc, chromium, co-Q10, and essential fats.  This is due to the fact that high sugar treats use up a lot of nutrients during digestion and they dont usually contain many nutrients themselves.  Increased sugar intake also causes us to crave sugar even more.\r\n\r\nGetting Started- Licking the sugar habit cannot be done overnight.  It  may take weeks or even months, but it is an important step in controlling mood issues, especially during the winter months when depression usually worsens.\r\n\r\nHere are some easy steps to get you started:\r\n\r\nDONT BUY IT!  If sugary snacks are in your home, children and adults are more likely to indulge.  Replace cookies and candy with fruits such as grapes, apples or even prunes.  These fruits help satisfy sugar cravings and contain many healthy nutrients.\r\n\r\nPLAN AHEAD.  Sugar cravings occur when you are tired or hungry.  Try to have 3 meals a day and high protein snacks to avoid energy drops and hunger.  Take your own snacks to work to avoid reaching for candy.\r\n\r\nBE REALISTIC.  Allow yourself to cut down sugar intake gradually so you dont feel deprived.   Start by replacing one sugary snack or beverage every day with a healthy alternative, and work from there.\r\n\r\nNEED MORE HELP? Schedule a free consult at the Wellness Center today!',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 16:17:34','2012-05-17 16:17:34',1),(16,'Lets Eat! Recipe for Gluten-Free Cranberry Almond Loaf','let-s-eat-recipe-for-gluten-free-cranberry-almond-loaf',NULL,'2011-11-29 00:00:00','**Gluten-Free Cranberry Almond Loaf**\r\n\r\n![](http://66.228.62.131/spree/uploads/285/original/loaf.jpg \"\")\r\n\r\n**Ingredients:**\r\n\r\n cup creamy roasted almond butter, at room temperature\r\n\r\n2 tablespoons olive oil\r\n\r\n3 large eggs\r\n\r\n cup arrowroot powder\r\n\r\n1 teaspoon salt\r\n\r\n teaspoon baking soda\r\n\r\n cup dried apricots, chopped into  inch pieces\r\n\r\n cup dried cranberries\r\n\r\n cup sesame seeds\r\n\r\n cup sunflower seeds\r\n\r\n cup pumpkin seeds\r\n\r\n cup sliced almonds, plus 2 tablespoons to sprinkle on top\r\n\r\nolive oil for greasing\r\n\r\nalmond flour for dusting\r\n\r\n**Directions:**\r\n\r\n- In a large bowl, blend almond butter, olive oil and eggs with a hand blender until smooth\r\n- In a medium bowl, combine arrowroot powder, salt and baking soda\r\n- Blend arrowroot mixture into wet ingredients until thoroughly combined\r\n- Fold in apricots, cranberries, seeds and sliced almonds\r\n- Grease a 3  x 7  x 2  inch loaf pan with olive oil and dust with almond flour\r\n- Pour batter into loaf pan and sprinkle remaining sliced almonds on top\r\n- Bake at 350 for 40-50 minutes until a knife inserted into center comes out clean\r\n- Let bread cool in pan for 1 hour, then serve',NULL,1,'2012-05-17 16:23:14','2012-05-21 18:42:53',1),(17,'Why you should buy Physiologics Brand','why-you-should-buy-physiologics-brand',NULL,'2011-12-02 00:00:00','Do you know whats in your supplements? We know wha