wn, in rat studies, to have a positive impact on total cholesterol and very low density lipoproteins (VLDL) by stimulating bile acid formation and excretion.] \r\nWhen compared to other vegetables, the yellow peas used in Peatein have low levels of phytosteroids (isoflavones), thus minimizing the possible estrogenic effects. \r\nPeatein: great protein source for athletes and anyone who is physically active \r\nDue to its favorable amino acid profile and high digestibility, Peatein is an excellent choice for consumption before, during, and after exercise. Adequate intake of protein, in particular BCAAs, helps to promote muscle growth and repair, particularly after strenuous resistance training. \r\nHypoallergenic\r\nThe pea protein in Peatein is not a major allergen, and is, therefore, a safe alternative for people with allergies to milk and milk products who must avoid casein or whey proteins, for those with lactose intolerance, and for vegetarians with soy allergies.\r\n','2012-06-01 00:00:00',NULL,'peatein-vanilla-450-g','Peatein, a natural pea protein concentrate, offers a high level of functionality and nutritional benefits. It is ideal for those who are looking for vegetarian protein and may not want dairy derived protein.','Peatein, a natural pea protein concentrate, offers a high level of functionality and nutritional benefits. It is ideal for those who are looking for vegetarian protein and may not want dairy derived protein.',2,1,'2012-05-18 18:07:22','2012-05-21 12:31:08',1000,0,1,NULL),(317,'Peatein Unflavored 450 grams','Peatein Unflavored/Unsweetened 450 g\r\nGreat-tasting vegetarian protein powder \r\nPeatein, a natural pea protein concentrate, offers a high level of functionality and nutritional benefits. It is ideal for those who are looking for vegetarian protein and may not want dairy derived protein. Peatein is a true vegan protein which has high bioavailability, excellent digestibility (98%), and is hypoallergenic. \r\nThe raw materials, North Am