men in these families using traditional stone querns; the oil is never factory-processed, thus its limited supply.\r\nLa Bedouines hand-ground Argan Oil is a lightweight, dry oil that is extraordinarily nutritive. It is 80% fatty acids and rich in Vitamin E tocopherols (twice the amount as olive oil) which raise the skins anti oxidant levels, carotenes known to rectify sun damage, squalene which protects the skin against free radicals, and ferulic acid, a skin cell regenerator.\r\nArgan Oils legendary anti-aging benefits have been substantiated in clinical trials and research studies in Europe, Morocco and the US.\r\nRepairs collagen fiber, Promotes oxygenation and moisture retention, Neutralizes free radicals, Improves and helps prevent acne, eczema and psoriasis, Regulates sebum production to reduce skin oiliness, Increases skin elasticity and tightening, Reduces the appearance of wrinkles\r\n','2012-08-20 00:00:00','2012-09-24 20:34:37','la-bedouine-beauty-ritual','','',2,1,'2012-08-20 04:44:22','2012-09-24 20:34:37',19,0,1,NULL),(489,'COPY OF Buffered Vitamin C Powder 300 gms*','Buffered Vitamin C Powder 300 gms \r\n(Cassava Root Source) \r\nCurrently on sale for $20.00 while supplies last (Retail price: $24.72)\r\nThe unique cassava source makes Buffered C Cassava root source well-tolerated by individuals unable to tolerate other sources of vitamin C. The product has exactly the same formula as #70000 and contains ascorbic acid and carbonates of calcium, magnesium and potassium, giving it an acid-alkaline buffering action (pH 7.0 in water) potentially improving bowel tolerance and minimizing hyperacidity. ','2012-04-18 00:00:00','2012-09-11 19:38:59','buffered-vitamin-c-powder-300-gms-1','The unique cassava source makes Buffered C Cassava root source well-tolerated by individuals unable to tolerate other sources of vitamin C.','vitamin c, bowel tolerance, Cassava Root Source',2,1,'2012-09-11 19:29:37','2012-09-11 19:38:59',0,0,1,NULL),(490,'Folic Acid B12 90 tabs','Folic Acid B12 90 tabs\r\nFolic acid and vitamin B12 support cellular health.\r\nEncourages healthy cell production\r\nSupports healthy nervous system development\r\nEncourages healthy circulation\r\nSupports healthy homocysteine levels\r\nAppropriate levels of folic acid aid in proper neural tube formation, reduce the risk of birth defects, and support proper nervous system development as a baby grows\r\nEssential in the important processes of DNA formation and replication','2012-09-18 00:00:00',NULL,'folic-acid-b12','','',2,1,'2012-09-18 16:27:30','2012-09-18 16:30:01',1000,0,1,NULL);
